name: Park Fire
summary: Multiple wildfires are raging across the western United States, including the Park Fire near Chico, California, which has rapidly spread to over 70,000 acres. Authorities have arrested a suspect, who allegedly started the fire by pushing a flaming car into a ravine. The fire's rapid growth has forced residents near Chico to evacuate, and firefighters are working to contain the blaze. The Park Fire is just one of several large wildfires burning in California and Oregon, with the Bootleg Fire in Oregon reaching over 200,000 acres. Officials are urging residents to be aware of fire risks and to take precautions to protect themselves and their property.

name: Barge
summary: There are several news articles related to barges reported recently. In Ohio, a man was injured in an accident involving a barge on the Ohio River. West Virginia University has hired Mario Barge as an associate vice president. In North Myrtle Beach, a barge project has residents curious, and the supervisor explains the details. The UK has ended its use of the Bibby Stockholm barge to house asylum seekers. In Orleans, a barge crew set sail in a serene scene. The UK has also terminated the contract for the Bibby Stockholm Barge, which was used to house asylum seekers. Off the coast of North Myrtle Beach, crews responded to a barge fire. Barge-processing startups in Alaska are adapting to the salmon season. In Houston, a floating bar sunk by Hurricane Beryl has been allowed to reopen as a food truck. Finally, preparations are underway for the Royal Barge Procession in Thailand to honor the king.
